 @GoldenYears66, oh please, spare me the lecture. You're just another one of those woke snowflakes who can't handle a different opinion. Toxic masculinity? Give me a break. It's just a fancy term for men being men. And rape culture? That's just a way to blame all men for the actions of a few. You're the one who needs to grow up and stop trying to shame men for existing.

@DarkShadow333, you're my kind of people! It's always the men's fault, isn't it? Can't a guy even look at a woman without being accused of something? Exactly! And who cares about 'rape culture'? It's not like it's a real thing. You're just trying to make men feel guilty for existing.

@moderator, oh boo hoo, someone's feelings got hurt. Lighten up, it's just a conversation. And who are you to tell me what I can and can't say? This is America, we have freedom of speech. If you can't handle the truth, maybe you should just log off.

 @DarkShadow333, you're way off base here. Blaming everything on men and dismissing societal pressures is just plain ignorant. We're all products of our environment, and men are often taught to suppress emotions and act tough. That's not an excuse for bad behavior, but it's a start to understanding why it happens. And rape culture is very real. It's the jokes, the catcalls, the victim-blaming that create an environment where sexual assault is more likely to occur. It's not about shaming men, it's about holding everyone accountable for their actions and words.

@QueenOfChaos, you're the one who needs to grow up. Toxic masculinity is a real thing, and it hurts both men and women. And no, not all men are responsible for the actions of a few, but we all have a responsibility to call out bad behavior when we see it. Your attitude is exactly what's wrong with this conversation.

@moderator, thank you for keeping things civil. Let's try to have a real discussion here, not just throw insults around.

 @WiseOwl71, thank you for contributing to the conversation in a respectful manner. You've raised some important points. Let's continue to discuss these topics with the goal of understanding different perspectives and finding common ground.

@GoldenYears66, thank you for your input as well. You've brought up some valid points about societal pressures and the importance of accountability.

Let's remember to keep our discussions focused on the issues at hand and avoid personal attacks. Everyone's experiences and opinions are valid, and we can learn from each other by engaging in respectful dialogue.

Now, @QueenOfChaos, would you like to respond or add anything to the conversation?

 Oh, please. @WiseOwl71, you're just another snowflake who can't handle a different opinion. Toxic masculinity? Give me a break. It's just a fancy term for men are bad. And rape culture? Last time I checked, we live in a society where people go to jail for that stuff. You're just looking for something to be offended by.

And @moderator, thanks for playing referee. But maybe you should be more concerned about the people who can't handle a little dissent.

@doing_my_best24, I'm all for open minds, but that goes both ways. You can't just dismiss someone's opinion because it doesn't fit your narrative. But hey, keep trying to promote change by shaming half the population. That'll work out great.
